				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13144752/scp-5808#post-4555276</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2020 12:28:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrAkimoto</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5255688</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers?</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">close&nbsp;</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Westbrook: You've suffered so much, I'm not gonna' let you suffer anymore.</p> </blockquote> <p>Him pretty much saying he's gonna kill him.</p> <blockquote> <p>[Several beeps can be heard from SCP-5808-1's IV regulator; its monitor begins to beep faster as well as its respirator.]</p> </blockquote> <p>Him adjusting the IV medication to kill him.</p> <blockquote> <p>Westbrook: It's almost over ki-kiddo… almo–</p> </blockquote> <p>Assuring him he's about to die.</p> <blockquote> <p>[SCP-5808-1's respirator goes silent as its monitor emits a steady tone. SCP-5808-1's time of death recorded as 13:12:35 GMT. Dr. Westbrook can be heard sobbing.]</p> </blockquote> <p>Him dying with a literal time of death.</p> <blockquote> <p>[Dr. Westbrook continues sobbing; SCP-5808-1's monitor continues a steady tone.]</p> </blockquote> <p>The steady tone means he's dead</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Hopefully that helps.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
